HEADWORD: Photoheliometer
<hw>Pho`to*he`li*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Photo-</ets> + <ets>heliometer</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A double-lens instrument for measuring slight
variations of the sun's diameter by photography, utilizing the common
chord of two overlapping images.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Photolithograph</ent>⟦br⟧
